INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('32560', '2', 'Cut the eggplant crossways into rounds about 1/3 to 1/2 inch thick, and cut each one into 6 to 8 even chunks.  Peel the onion, and chop into 8 portions.  Trim the zucchini, and cut into thick slices.'),
('32560', '3', 'Heat grill pan over a high heat with a generous splash of olive oil.  When it is very hot, add all the vegetables to the pan.  Press down occasionally to get grill lines across them. Turn occasionally to prevent burning.  Cook for about 15 minutes, or until the vegetables are evenly browned and cooked through.'),
('32560', '4', 'Stir broad beans into the vegetables.'),
('32560', '5', 'Add chopped tomatoes, and vinegar.  Simmer for a few minutes while the couscous is prepared.'),
('32560', '6', 'Place couscous into a medium bowl.'),
('32560', '7', 'Add boiling vegetable stock, and stir with a fork. Keep lifting the couscous occasionally to prevent it sticking.  It only takes 2 to 3 minutes to become soft.'),
('32560', '8', 'Place couscous in a large bowl or serving platter, and serve the vegetables on top.'),
('32564', '1', 'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('32564', '2', 'Add rice, stir, and adjust heat to maintain a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally to prevent any grains from sticking to the pot, until the rice is just barely done, about 15 minutes. It will continue to cook as it cools.'),
('32564', '3', 'Drain the rice well and spread it out on a tray to cool quickly.'),
('32564', '4', 'Bring another large pot of salted water to a boil. Holding an asparagus spear in both hands, bend the spear until it breaks naturally at the point where it becomes tough. Repeat with the remaining spears. Discard the tough ends and cut the tender part into 1/3-inch lengths. Blanch asparagus and peas together in the boiling water for 1 minute and 30 seconds, then lift out with a strainer and transfer to a paper towel lined baking sheet to cool.'),
('32564', '5', 'Shell the fava beans, then blanch the unpeeled beans in the same boiling water for about 3 minutes.'),
('32564', '6', 'Drain, transfer them to a paper towel lined baking sheet to cool. Peel the fava beans by pinching open the loose skin. the peeled bean should slip out easily.'),
('32564', '7', 'Put the lemon juice in a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Gradually whisk in the olive oil.'),
('32564', '8', 'In a large bowl, combine the cooled rice, asparagus, peas, fava beans, basil, parsley, lemon zest, ham and cheese. Toss with your hands to blend.'),
('32564', '9', 'Pour the dressing over the salad (you may not need it all) and toss gently. Taste and adjust seasoning.'),
('32571', '1', 'Put the stock, carrots, and parsnips in a large saucepan over high heat and bring to a boil. Cook for 5 minutes or until the vegetables are crisp-tender. Strain in a sieve over a bowl, and reserve the stock and vegetables.'),
('32571', '2', 'Melt the butter in another saucepan over medium heat.'),
('32571', '3', 'Add the onion and celery, and cook, stirring often, for 5 minutes or until softened. Sprinkle in the flour and stir for 1 minute.'),
('32571', '4', 'Gradually stir in the reserved stock and bring to a boil, stirring. Reduce the heat and simmer for 2 minutes. Stir in the fava beans and mustard, and season with salt and pepper.'),
('32571', '5', 'Remove from the heat and cool until tepid. Stir in the chicken, cream, and reserved vegetables.'),
('32571', '6', 'Pour into a 9.5in (24cm) deep-dish pie pan.'),
('32571', '7', 'Preheat the oven to 400F (200C).'),
('32571', '8', 'Roll out the pastry on a lightly floured surface until about 1/8 in (3mm) thick.'),
('32571', '9', 'Cut out a round of dough slightly larger than the dish.'),
('32571', '10', 'Brush the dish rim with water, then position the pastry over the filling, and fold over the excess pastry so the dough is double-thick around the circumference of the pan. Crimp the pastry, glaze the top with the some beaten egg, and cut a small hole in the top.'),
('32571', '11', 'Place the pie on a baking sheet.'),
('32571', '12', 'Bake for 25 minutes or until the pastry is puffed and golden, and the filling is hot.'),
('32571', '13', 'Let cool for a few minutes, then serve.'),
('32572', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 30'),
('32572', '2', 'Combine the fennel, coriander and cumin seeds in a spice grinder and grind to a powder.'),
('32572', '3', 'Transfer to a small bowl and stir in the rosemary. Season the lamb chops with salt and coat with the spice mixture. refrigerate for 1 hour.'),
('32572', '4', 'In a shallow glass or ceramic baking dish, toss the cherry tomatoes with 1/4 cup of the olive oil and the garlic, bay leaves, thyme sprigs, vinegar and shallot.'),
('32572', '5', 'Add a pinch of salt and bake for about 30 minutes, until the tomatoes are soft.'),
('32572', '6', 'Meanwhile, bring a medium saucepan of salted water to a boil.'),
('32572', '7', 'Add the peas and cook until just tender, about 3 minutes. With a slotted spoon, transfer the peas to a bowl.'),
('32572', '8', 'Add the fava beans to the pan and cook until bright green, about 1 minute.'),
('32572', '9', 'Drain the favas and squeeze each one lightly to pop the bean from its skin.'),
('32572', '10', 'Add the favas to the peas.'),
('32572', '11', 'In a large skillet, heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil until shimmering.'),
('32572', '12', 'Add the chanterelles, season with salt and cook over moderately high heat until softened, 3 minutes. Reduce the heat to moderate and cook, stirring occasionally, until the chanterelles are tender and browned, about 5 minutes longer.'),
('32572', '13', 'Add 1 tablespoon of the butter and the pearl onions, cut side down, and cook over moderate heat until golden on the bottom, 3 minutes.'),
('32572', '14', 'Add the chicken stock and simmer over moderate heat until the pearl onions are tender, about 3 minutes longer. Stir the peas and fava beans into the skillet.'),
('32572', '15', 'Light a grill. Discard the bay leaves and thyme sprigs.'),
('32572', '16', 'Add the tomato mixture to the vegetable ragout and simmer for 3 minutes.'),
('32572', '17', 'Remove from the heat and stir in the mint, tarragon and marjoram.'),
('32572', '18', 'Add the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter, 1 tablespoon at a time, stirring until melted. Season the ragout with salt and pepper.'),
('32572', '19', 'Grill the lamb chops over high heat until nicely charred on the outside and medium-rare within, about 3 minutes per side. Spoon the ragout into 4 shallow bowls, top with the lamb chops and serve.'),
('32578', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('32578', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F. Lightly grease a 7 by 4 by 3-inch loaf pan with oil.'),
('32578', '3', 'In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, 1 cup of the evaporated cane juice, the potato starch, arrowroot, baking powder, baking soda, xanthan gum, salt, and 1 tablespoon of the cinnamon.'),
('32578', '4', 'Add the oil, applesauce, vanilla, and 1 cup of hot water to the dry ingredients. Stir until the batter is smooth.'),
('32578', '5', 'Transfer 1/4 cup of the batter to a small bowl, and add the remaining 1/4 cup of the evaporated cane juice, 1 tablespoon of cinnamon, and the remaining hot water. Stir until the mixture is creamy.'),
('32578', '6', 'Pour contents of the medium bowl into the prepared loaf pan. Carefully drizzle the batter from the small bowl down the center of the loaf. To create the swirl, take a teaspoon and, starting from 1 end of the loaf pan, move down the length of the pan as you swirl the spoon up and down through the batter. Sprinkle the top with evaporated cane juice.'),
('32578', '7', 'Put the pan in the oven on the center rack and bake for 25 minutes.'),
('32578', '8', 'Remove from the oven and brush the top with a generous amount of oil. Return it to the oven and bake for another 15 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean and the crust is crunchy.'),
('32578', '9', 'Let the teacake cool in the pan for 20 minutes, then gently run a knife around the edge of the cake. Cover the top of the pan with a cutting board, and invert the cake onto the board. Carefully lift the pan away and re-invert the Teacake onto another cutting board. Either cut and serve warm, or wait until it is completely cool before storing. Cover the uncut teacake with plastic wrap and store at room temperature for up to 3 days.'),
('32579', '1', 'Fry the onion and add the garlic once the onion is translucent.'),
('32579', '2', 'Add the tomatoes and the tomato puree'),
('32579', '3', 'Add the herbs and spices.Crush the stock cube and add to the sauce.Taste for seasoning and add the sugar.Cook on medium heat until sauce begins to thicken.'),
('32579', '4', 'Add the tuna and broad beans.Cook on medium heat for as long as it takes you to boil the spaghetti, this way you''re allowing the broad beans to absorb the flavours.Boil the spaghetti and add it to the sauce.'),
('32579', '5', 'Add the chopped olives and on a very low heat incorporate the sauce into the pasta until every strand is well coated.'),
('32579', '6', 'Serve with some Parmesan cheese and enjoy!'),
('32610', '1', 'Place the chopped onion, ginger, garlic, and 4 tablespoons of water into a blender.  Puree until smooth.'),
('32610', '2', 'Spread the cut-up chicken out on a plate.  Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper and let sit.'),
('32610', '3', 'Place the flour in a bowl.  Slowly add 1 cup of the chicken broth to mix well.'),
('32610', '4', 'Heat a skillet over medium-high heat and add the oil.  When the oil is hot, toss in the chicken and stir-fry until lightly browned.  Some of the fat will render from the chicken skin.'),
('32610', '5', 'Remove the chicken with a slotted spoon.'),
('32610', '6', 'Add the sliced onions to the pan and cook slowly, allowing the onions to caramelize over the course of five to seven minutes.  Towards the end of that time when the onions are beginning to brown, add the turmeric and paprika.'),
('32610', '7', 'In a pot suited for soups, add the chicken along with the juices that will have settled, the sauteed onions, the onion and ginger puree, and the remaining 2 cups of chicken broth.  Carefully add the chickpea flour and broth mixture, mixing quickly so that the flour won''t clump.'),
('32610', '8', 'Bring the pot to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer gently, uncovered, for 15 minutes.  Season to taste with more salt, if needed.'),
('32610', '9', 'Add the coconut milk.  Stir to mix and return to a simmer.'),
('32610', '10', 'Serve with noodles and garnishes as desired.'),
('32618', '1', 'Bring a pot of water to a boil, then add the fava beans and cook until just tender, 2 to 4 minutes.'),
('32618', '2', 'Drain the fava beans in a colander and place it under cold running water until the beans are cool enough to handle. Gently peel the skins off the beans. Set the beans aside.'),
('32618', '3', 'Drain the acidulated water form the artichokes and cut each heart crosswise into -inch-thick slices, including the stems. Rub the slices with the cut side of the lemon halves to prevent discoloring, then set aside.'),
('32618', '4', 'Heat the olive oil in a heavy 4-quart saucepan over medium heat.'),
('32618', '5', 'Add the onion and ham and cook, stirring, until the onion is limp, about 5 minutes.'),
('32618', '6', 'Add half of the garlic and the sliced artichokes and cook, stirring, for about 1 minute. Partially cover the pan and continue cooking until the artichokes are almost tender, 5 to 7 minutes, adjusting the heat so that the artichokes cook without browning.'),
('32618', '7', 'Add the potato and green beans and cook for 1 minute.'),
('32618', '8', 'Add enough stock to barely cover the vegetables and season with salt and pepper to taste. Reduce the heat to very low and simmer the stew, partially covered, until all the vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.'),
('32618', '9', 'Add the fava beans and cook until tender, about 5 minutes longer.'),
('32618', '10', 'Place the parsley and the remaining garlic in a mortar and, using a pestle, mash them to a paste.'),
('32618', '11', 'Add the parsley mixture to the stew. Taste for seasoning, adding more salt and/or pepper as necessary and the lemon juice if desired. Cook the stew until the flavors meld, another minute or so.'),
('32618', '12', 'Let the stew cool to warm and serve.'),
('32618', '13', 'var article'),
('32618', '14', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('32618', '15', 'article'),
('32618', '16', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('32627', '1', 'In a bowl, toss the onion with 1 tablespoon of the flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.'),
('32627', '2', 'Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons of the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook the onion, stirring, until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes. transfer to a plate.Wipe out the skillet and heat the remaining tablespoon of oil over medium-high heat. Cook mushrooms, stirring, until tender, 5 to 6 minutes.Reduce heat to medium. Sprinkle the remaining tablespoon of flour over the mushrooms and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.'),
('32627', '3', 'Add the milk and 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Simmer, stirring, until mixture begins to thicken, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('32627', '4', 'Add green beans and cook until heated through, 3 to 4 minutes. Top with the onions.'),
('32631', '1', 'Heat a large skillet over medium high heat, cook bacon and set aside on paper towels.Cook chicken in remaining bacon grease.'),
('32631', '2', 'Add butter or ghee to the pan if there is not enough grease.'),
('32631', '3', 'Add garlic and onions and reduce heat to medium, stirring until the garlic and onions are tender.'),
('32631', '4', 'Add in green beans, and cooked bacon, cover and let simmer for about 5 minutes.  Stir in cheese and coconut milk until mixed well.'),
('32638', '1', 'Bring a large pot of water to a boil.'),
('32638', '2', 'Add the green beans and salt and cook just until tender, about 4 to 6 minutes.'),
('32638', '3', 'Drain well in a colander.'),
('32638', '4', 'In the same pot, over medium-high heat, combine the butter and pine nuts. Cook, stirring frequently, until the pine nuts are lightly toasted, about 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('32638', '5', 'Add the beans. toss to stir well. Season to taste with salt and freshly ground pepper.'),
('32640', '1', 'Boil green beans until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.'),
('32640', '2', 'Drain and run under cold water. Reserve 1/4 of the beans for another use. Toss the rest of the beans with fresh lime juice, olive oil, and freshly grated ginger. Season to taste with kosher salt and freshly ground pepper.'),
('32658', '1', 'Rinse and drain beans. trim and discard stem ends. In each of two 12- by 17-inch baking pans, mix half the beans with half the oil. spread level.'),
('32658', '2', 'Bake in a 450 regular or convection oven until beans are slightly browned and tender when pierced, 15 to 25 minutes. switch pan positions halfway through baking.'),
('32658', '3', 'Stir half the nuts and butter into beans in each pan. continue baking until nuts are golden, 5 to 6 minutes longer.'),
('32658', '4', 'Pour into a bowl, add 1/4 teaspoon cayenne, and mix well. Taste and add more cayenne and salt if desired.'),
('32660', '1', 'In a large pot of lightly salted boiling water, cook the beans until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.'),
('32660', '2', 'Drain and run under cold water to stop the cooking.'),
('32660', '3', 'Meanwhile, toast the walnuts in a skillet over medium heat until lightly golden, 6 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally. Reserve half the walnuts and crush the remainder in a resealable plastic bag with a meat pounder or rolling pin. In a large bowl, whisk together the oil, lemon juice, salt, and a few grinds of pepper.'),
('32660', '4', 'Add the crushed walnuts, whole walnuts, and beans and toss to coat well.'),
('32660', '5', 'Serve cold or at room temperature. (Can be made up to 1 day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.)'),
('32662', '1', 'Bring a large pot of water to a boil.'),
('32662', '2', 'Add the green beans and cook, uncovered, until crisp-tender, 3 to 4 minutes.'),
('32662', '3', 'Drain and set aside.'),
('32662', '4', 'In a large bowl, whisk together the remaining ingredients until well blended.'),
('32662', '5', 'Add the green beans and toss to combine well. Season to taste with freshly ground pepper.'),
('32665', '1', 'In a saucepan, combine white vinegar, water, sugar, black peppercorns, garlic cloves, and salt and bring to a boil.'),
('32665', '2', 'Remove from heat and let sit for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, combine radishes, green beans, and the zest of 1 lemon in a large bowl.'),
('32665', '3', 'Add the vinegar mixture and let sit 15 minutes.'),
('32665', '4', 'Serve the remaining pickles with the polenta.'),
('32672', '1', 'Pack beans into hot jars, trimming to fit 1/2 inch from top.'),
('32672', '2', 'Add 1 pepper, 1 garlic clove (quartered), 1/2 teaspoon mustard seeds, and 1/2 teaspoon dill seeds to each jar.'),
('32672', '3', 'Bring vinegar, 5 cups water, and pickling salt to a boil. pour into each jar, filling to 1/2 inch from top.'),
('32672', '4', 'Remove air bubbles. wipe jar rims. Cover at once with metal lids. screw on bands.'),
('32672', '5', 'Process in a boiling-water bath 10 minutes. 1 3/4 teaspoons dried crushed red pepper may be substituted for hot red peppers.'),
('32672', '6', 'Add 1/4 teaspoon per jar.'),
('32673', '1', 'Fill a large bowl with ice water. In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook the beans until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes.'),
('32673', '2', 'Drain the beans and transfer them to the ice water to cool.'),
('32673', '3', 'Drain and pat dry.'),
('32673', '4', 'In a large skillet, heat the olive oil.'),
('32673', '5', 'Add the garlic and cook over moderately high heat until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Stir in the ground ginger and crushed red pepper, then add the beans. Season with salt and stir-fry until the garlic is lightly browned and the beans are tender, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('32673', '6', 'Transfer the beans to a platter and serve.'),
('32676', '1', 'Bring a medium pot of water to a boil, add green beans, and cook until bright green, about 3 minutes.'),
('32676', '2', 'Drain and rinse with cold water. In a small bowl, mix lime juice, soy sauce, and pepper, then set aside.'),
('32676', '3', 'Cut tofu into 1/2-in.-thick rectangles.'),
('32676', '4', 'Heat oil in a nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat.'),
('32676', '5', 'Add tofu, sprinkle with sugar, and cook, turning occasionally, until evenly browned, about 10 minutes. Stir in shallots and cook until browned, about 3 minutes.'),
('32676', '6', 'Add green beans and cook until warmed, about 3 minutes.'),
('32676', '7', 'Pour in soy mixture and stir to coat.'),
('32677', '1', 'Rinse and drain green beans. trim off and discard stem ends.'),
('32677', '2', 'Cut beans into 2- to 3-inch lengths. In a small bowl, mix soy sauce, rice vinegar, sugar, chili flakes, and white pepper.'),
('32677', '3', 'Set a 10- to 12-inch frying pan over high heat. When pan is hot, add beans and 1/4 cup water. Cover and cook, stirring once, until beans are bright green and slightly crunchy to bite, 3 to 4 minutes. Uncover and cook until any remaining water has evaporated.'),
('32677', '4', 'Add oil, garlic, and ginger to pan. stir until green beans and garlic are lightly browned, 1 to 2 minutes. Stir soy mixture and add to pan. bring to a boil and stir until most of the liquid has evaporated and the sauce thickens and coats the beans, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('32677', '5', 'Pour into a serving dish.'),
('32677', '6', 'Serve hot or cool.'),
('32681', '1', 'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('32681', '2', 'Add the green beans and cook until just tender, 4 to 6 minutes.'),
('32681', '3', 'Drain and transfer to a serving bowl.Meanwhile, brown the butter: Melt the butter in a skillet or small saucepan over medium heat. Swirl or stir the butter with a wooden spoon as it starts to foam and sputter.'),
('32681', '4', 'Remove the butter from the heat as soon as it begins to turn golden brown and smells nutty, about 1 minute..'),
('32681', '5', 'Add the lemon juice, almonds, and salt. Swirl skillet over heat for 30 seconds more to toast the almonds. Spoon the mixture over the green beans.'),
('32682', '1', 'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('32682', '2', 'Add the green beans and cook until just tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('32682', '3', 'Add the garlic and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.'),
('32682', '4', 'Add the pine nuts and cook until golden brown, about 3 minutes.'),
('32682', '5', 'Drain the green beans and transfer to the skillet.'),
('32682', '6', 'Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and toss to coat.'),
('32682', '7', 'Transfer to a serving bowl.Make-Ahead Note: This dish can be partially prepared up to 2 days in advance. Blanch the green beans by boiling until tender. Plunge them into an ice bath to stop the cooking.'),
('32682', '8', 'Drain and refrigerate, covered, until ready to saut with the garlic and pine nuts. Cook the green beans until heated through.'),
('32684', '1', 'Soak the dried porcini mushrooms in the water for 20 minutes.Meanwhile, melt the butter in a pan over medium heat.'),
('32684', '2', 'Add the onions and saute until tender, about 4-6 minutes.'),
('32684', '3', 'Add the garlic and thyme and saute until fragrant, about a minutes.'),
('32684', '4', 'Add the cremini mushrooms and saute until the start to caramelized and turn golden brown, about 10-15 minutes.'),
('32684', '5', 'Add the porcini mushrooms and the water they were soaking in to the pan and simmer at medium-high until reduced by half, about 10 minutes.'),
('32684', '6', 'Add the cream and parmigiano reggiano, season with salt and pepper and simmer until it thickens, about 2-4 minutes.Meanwhile steam the green beans.'),
('32684', '7', 'Remove the mushrooms from the heat and mix in the parsley.'),
('32684', '8', 'Serve the green beans covered in the mushroom sauce.'),
('32688', '1', 'Steam green beans, covered, 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),
('32688', '2', 'Remove from steamer. toss with remaining ingredients.'),
('32690', '1', 'In a large skillet, over medium heat, heat the butter and 2 tablespoons of the oil.'),
('32690', '2', 'Add the onion, sugar, and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 25 minutes.'),
('32690', '3', 'Add the vinegar. Cook, stirring, for 1 minute.'),
('32690', '4', 'Add the remaining oil, 1/4 teaspoon of the salt, and the pepper.'),
('32690', '5', 'Transfer half the mixture to a blender and puree, then return to skillet.Meanwhile, cook the green beans with the remaining 1/4 teaspoon of salt in boiling water until tender, about 4 minutes.'),
('32690', '6', 'Transfer to a bowl of ice water.'),
('32690', '7', 'Drain and pat dry.'),
('32690', '8', 'Transfer to a serving bowl, toss with the onion mixture, and sprinkle with the zest.Make Ahead: Cook the green beans and make the vinaigrette early in the day. refrigerate them separately.'),
('32690', '9', 'Combine them just before serving.'),
('32691', '1', 'Pour olive oil into a 12-inch frying pan or 14-inch wok over medium-high heat.'),
('32691', '2', 'Add green beans and stir often until tender-crisp and lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes.'),
('32691', '3', 'Add garlic and stir just until fragrant, 1 minute.'),
('32691', '4', 'Add wine, lime juice, and salt and pepper to taste. stir until liquid boils, 1 minute.'),
('32691', '5', 'Pour into a serving dish and sprinkle with Manchego cheese.'),
('32691', '6', 'Serve hot.'),
('32694', '1', 'In a small bowl, stir together the teriyaki sauce, honey, and butter.'),
('32694', '2', 'Fill a bowl with cold water and ice cubes.'),
('32694', '3', 'Bring a large pot of water to a boil and add the lemon juice. Drop in the beans and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, or until beans are bright green.'),
('32694', '4', 'Drain the beans in a colander and then plunge them into the iced water.'),
('32694', '5', 'Drain again and set aside.'),
('32694', '6', 'In a skillet, cook the bacon until very crispy, crumble and set aside.'),
('32694', '7', 'Saute the bell pepper and onion in the hot bacon fat for 2 minutes.'),
('32694', '8', 'Add the beans, cashews, and bacon to the skillet.'),
('32694', '9', 'Add the teriyaki-honey sauce and toss gently.'),
('32696', '1', 'Cook beans in boiling water 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),
('32696', '2', 'Drain and rinse with cold water. drain.'),
('32696', '3', 'Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Cook 1 minute or until lightly browned.'),
('32696', '4', 'Add beans, juice, and savory to pan, tossing to coat. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('32698', '1', 'Prepare a large bowl of ice water. Set aside.'),
('32698', '2', 'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('32698', '3', 'Add the green beans and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, until crisp-tender.'),
('32698', '4', 'Drain the green beans, then submerge them in the ice water for 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('32698', '5', 'In a large nonstick skillet, heat the olive oil over medium-high heat.'),
('32698', '6', 'Add the mushrooms, onion, and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, until the mushrooms are nicely browned, about 10 to 11 minutes.'),
('32698', '7', 'Add the wine and cook for 1 minute.'),
('32698', '8', 'Add the green beans and thyme and cook until heated through. When done, remove from the heat, add the butter, and toss to combine. Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('32698', '9', 'Serve warm.'),
('32701', '1', 'Cook the green beans in the microwave according to package instructions'),
('32701', '2', 'Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('32701', '3', 'Add the garlic, Italian seasoning, red pepper flakes, a generous pinch of salt and pepper and saute for 2 minutes.'),
('32701', '4', 'Add the green beans, toss to coat them in the oil and saute another 2 minutes.'),
('32701', '5', 'Serve hot.'),
('32706', '1', 'Steam green beans 5 minutes.'),
('32706', '2', 'Drizzle with olive oil. sprinkle with chopped thyme, chopped chives, and salt.'),
('32712', '1', 'Bring 3 cups water to a boil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Stir in bouillon cube until dissolved.'),
('32712', '2', 'Add green beans, and cook 4 to 6 minutes or until crisp-tender. drain.'),
('32712', '3', 'Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('32712', '4', 'Add onion, garlic, and ginger. saut 2 minutes.'),
('32712', '5', 'Add beans, salt, and pepper. saut 1 minute or until thoroughly heated.'),
('32712', '6', 'Transfer to a serving dish, and sprinkle with pecans.'),
('32712', '7', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('32712', '8', 'NOTE: For testing purposes only, we used Knorr bouillon cubes.'),
('32716', '1', 'Bring 3 cups water to a boil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Stir in bouillon cube until dissolved.'),
('32716', '2', 'Add green beans, and cook 4 to 6 minutes or until crisp-tender. drain.'),
('32716', '3', 'Melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('32716', '4', 'Add onion, garlic, and ginger. saut 2 minutes.'),
('32716', '5', 'Add beans, salt, and pepper. saut 1 minute or until thoroughly heated.'),
('32716', '6', 'Transfer to a serving dish, and sprinkle with pecans.'),
('32716', '7', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('32716', '8', 'NOTE: For testing purposes only, we used Knorr bouillon cubes.'),
('32721', '1', 'Place first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven. cover and cook over medium heat 30 minutes.'),
('32721', '2', 'Drain.'),
('32721', '3', 'Melt butter in Dutch oven. add garlic and lemon pepper, and saut mixture over medium heat 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('32721', '4', 'Add green beans, and saut 5 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley.'),
('32722', '1', 'Arrange green beans in a steamer basket over boiling water. Cover and steam 5 to 7 minutes. Plunge into ice water to stop the cooking process. drain.'),
('32722', '2', 'Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. add shallots, and saut 3 minutes or until tender.'),
