('32735', '3', 'Place green beans, onion, and 3 Tbsp. water in a microwave-safe bowl. Cover bowl tightly with plastic wrap, folding back a small edge to allow steam to escape.'),
('32735', '4', 'Microwave at HIGH 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. drain. Toss together hot beans and sliced onion, brown butter mixture, and salt. sprinkle with cracked pepper.'),
('32737', '1', 'In a medium bowl, combine the water with the sugar, sake, miso, soy sauce, vinegar, cornstarch and chile-garlic sauce.'),
('32737', '2', 'Heat a large, deep skillet for 2 minutes.'),
('32737', '3', 'Add the oil and heat until smoking.'),
('32737', '4', 'Add the green beans and scallions and cook over high heat, stirring occasionally, until just tender and browned in spots, about 6 minutes. Stir the sauce mixture, add it to the beans and bring to a boil. Cook until the sauce is glossy and slightly thickened, about 1 minute. Stir in the sesame oil.'),
('32737', '5', 'Transfer the beans to a platter and garnish with the sesame seeds.'),
('32737', '6', 'Serve with the tortilla wedges for wrapping.'),
('32739', '1', 'Melt 3 tablespoons butter in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('32739', '2', 'Add shiitake mushrooms and saute until tender, about 5 minutes.'),
